    11import csv
    12from datetime import datetime
    13from collections import defaultdict, Counter
    14import statistics
    15from typing import Dict, List, Any

    18def load_data(filename: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:
    19    """Load and parse sales data from CSV file.
    20
    21    Args:
    22        filename: Path to CSV file
    23
    24    Returns:
    25        List of dictionaries containing parsed sales records
    26    """
    27    rows = []
    28    with open(filename, 'r') as f:
    29        reader = csv.DictReader(f)
    30        for row in reader:
    31            rows.append({
    32                'date': row['date'],
    33                'product': row['product'],
    34                'category': row['category'],
    35                'quantity': int(row['quantity']),
    36                'unit_price': float(row['unit_price']),
    37                'total_sales': float(row['total_sales']),
    38                'region': row['region'],
    39                'salesperson': row['salesperson']
    40            })
    41    return rows
    42

    44def print_section(title: str, char: str = "="):
    45    """Print formatted section header."""
    46    print(f"\n{char * 80}")
    47    print(f"{title.center(80)}")
    48    print(f"{char * 80}\n")
    49

    51def print_subsection(title: str):
    52    """Print formatted subsection header."""
    53    print(f"\n{title}")
    54    print("-" * len(title))

    57def calculate_descriptive_stats(values: List[float]) -> Dict[str, float]:
    58    """Calculate comprehensive descriptive statistics.
    59
    60    Args:
    61        values: List of numeric values
    62
    63    Returns:
    64        Dictionary containing mean, median, std dev, min, max, quartiles
    65    """
    66    if not values:
    67        return {}
    68
    69    sorted_values = sorted(values)
    70    n = len(values)
    71
    72    return {
    73        'count': n,
    74        'sum': sum(values),
    75        'mean': statistics.mean(values),
    76        'median': statistics.median(values),
    77        'std_dev': statistics.stdev(values) if n > 1 else 0,
    78        'min': min(values),
    79        'max': max(values),
    80        'q1': sorted_values[n // 4],
    81        'q3': sorted_values[(3 * n) // 4],
    82        'range': max(values) - min(values)
    83    }
    84

    86def data_quality_check(rows: List[Dict]) -> Dict[str, Any]:
    87    """Perform comprehensive data quality checks.
    88
    89    Args:
    90        rows: List of sales records
    91
    92    Returns:
    93        Dictionary containing quality check results
    94    """
    95    issues = []
    96    warnings = []
    97
    98    # Check for missing values
    99    for i, row in enumerate(rows):
   100        for key, value in row.items():
   101            if value is None or value == '':
   102                issues.append(f"Row {i+1}: Missing value in column '{key}'")
   103
   104    # Validate calculations
   105    calculation_errors = 0
   106    for i, row in enumerate(rows):
   107        expected = round(row['quantity'] * row['unit_price'], 2)
   108        actual = round(row['total_sales'], 2)
   109        if abs(expected - actual) > 0.02:  # Allow for rounding errors
   110            calculation_errors += 1
   111            warnings.append(
   112                f"Row {i+1}: Calculation mismatch - "
   113                f"{row['quantity']}  ${row['unit_price']} = ${expected}, "
   114                f"but total_sales = ${actual}"
   115            )
   116
   117    # Check for negative values
   118    for i, row in enumerate(rows):
   119        if row['quantity'] < 0:
   120            issues.append(f"Row {i+1}: Negative quantity ({row['quantity']})")
   121        if row['unit_price'] < 0:
   122            issues.append(f"Row {i+1}: Negative unit price ({row['unit_price']})")
   123        if row['total_sales'] < 0:
   124            issues.append(f"Row {i+1}: Negative total sales ({row['total_sales']})")
   125
   126    # Check for outliers (values > 3 std deviations from mean)
   127    sales_values = [row['total_sales'] for row in rows]
   128    if len(sales_values) > 1:
   129        mean_sales = statistics.mean(sales_values)
   130        std_sales = statistics.stdev(sales_values)
   131        threshold = 3 * std_sales
   132
   133        outliers = []
   134        for i, row in enumerate(rows):
   135            if abs(row['total_sales'] - mean_sales) > threshold:
   136                outliers.append(f"Row {i+1}: {row['product']} - ${row['total_sales']:,.2f}")
   137
   138        if outliers:
   139            warnings.append(f"Found {len(outliers)} statistical outliers (>3 std dev)")
   140
   141    return {
   142        'total_rows': len(rows),
   143        'issues': issues,
   144        'warnings': warnings,
   145        'calculation_errors': calculation_errors,
   146        'is_clean': len(issues) == 0
   147    }
   148

   174    if quality['warnings']:
   175        print(f"\n {len(quality['warnings'])} warnings:")

   224def analyze_by_category(rows: List[Dict]):
   225    """Analyze sales data by product category."""
   226    print_section("3. CATEGORY ANALYSIS")
   227
   228    category_data = defaultdict(lambda: {
   229        'sales': [],
   230        'quantity': [],
   231        'transactions': 0,
   232        'products': set()
   233    })
   234
   235    for row in rows:
   236        cat = row['category']
   237        category_data[cat]['sales'].append(row['total_sales'])
   238        category_data[cat]['quantity'].append(row['quantity'])
   239        category_data[cat]['transactions'] += 1
   240        category_data[cat]['products'].add(row['product'])
   241
   242    for category in sorted(category_data.keys()):
   243        data = category_data[category]
   244        stats = calculate_descriptive_stats(data['sales'])
   245
   246        print_subsection(f"{category}")
   247        print(f"Total Revenue:       ${stats['sum']:,.2f} ({stats['sum']/sum(r['total_sales'] for r in rows)*100:.1f}%)")
   248        print(f"Transactions:        {data['transactions']} ({data['transactions']/len(rows)*100:.1f}%)")
   249        print(f"Unique Products:     {len(data['products'])}")
   250        print(f"Total Units:         {sum(data['quantity']):,}")
   251        print(f"Avg Transaction:     ${stats['mean']:,.2f}")
   252        print(f"Median Transaction:  ${stats['median']:,.2f}")
   253        print(f"Avg Units/Order:     {statistics.mean(data['quantity']):.1f}")

   256def analyze_by_region(rows: List[Dict]):

   267    for row in rows:

   269        region_data[region]['sales'].append(row['total_sales'])
   270        region_data[region]['quantity'].append(row['quantity'])
   271        region_data[region]['transactions'] += 1
   272        region_data[region]['categories'][row['category']] += 1
   273
   274    # Sort by total sales
   275    total_sales_all = sum(row['total_sales'] for row in rows)
   276    sorted_regions = sorted(

   283        stats = calculate_descriptive_stats(data['sales'])
   284
   285        print_subsection(f"{region} Region")

   287        print(f"Transactions:        {data['transactions']}")
   288        print(f"Total Units:         {sum(data['quantity']):,}")
   289        print(f"Avg Transaction:     ${stats['mean']:,.2f}")
   290        print(f"Median Transaction:  ${stats['median']:,.2f}")
   291        print(f"Category Mix:        ", end="")
   292        for cat, count in data['categories'].most_common():
   293            print(f"{cat} ({count})", end=" ")

   396def analyze_time_trends(rows: List[Dict]):

   413    daily_sales = [data['sales'] for data in daily_data.values()]
   414    stats = calculate_descriptive_stats(daily_sales)
   415

   421    print(f"Worst Day Sales:     ${stats['min']:,.2f}")
   422

   424    top_days = sorted(

   434def analyze_cross_tabulations(rows: List[Dict]):
   435    """Perform cross-tabulation analysis."""
   436    print_section("8. CROSS-TABULATION ANALYSIS")
   437
   438    # Category  Region
   439    print_subsection("Revenue by Category  Region")
   440    cross_tab = defaultdict(lambda: defaultdict(float))
   441
   442    for row in rows:
   443        cross_tab[row['category']][row['region']] += row['total_sales']
   444
   445    # Print header
   446    regions = sorted(set(row['region'] for row in rows))
   447    print(f"{'Category':<15}", end="")
   448    for region in regions:
   449        print(f"{region:>12}", end="")
   450    print(f"{'Total':>12}")
   451    print("-" * (15 + 12 * (len(regions) + 1)))
   452
   453    # Print data
   454    for category in sorted(cross_tab.keys()):
   455        print(f"{category:<15}", end="")
   456        total = 0
   457        for region in regions:
   458            value = cross_tab[category][region]
   459            total += value
   460            print(f"${value:>10,.0f}", end=" ")
   461        print(f"${total:>10,.0f}")
   462

   464def generate_summary_insights(rows: List[Dict]):
   465    """Generate key insights and summary statistics."""
   466    print_section("9. KEY INSIGHTS & SUMMARY")
   467
   468    total_revenue = sum(row['total_sales'] for row in rows)
   469    total_units = sum(row['quantity'] for row in rows)
   470
   471    # Category breakdown
   472    cat_revenue = defaultdict(float)
   473    for row in rows:
   474        cat_revenue[row['category']] += row['total_sales']
   475
   476    top_category = max(cat_revenue.items(), key=lambda x: x[1])
   477
   478    # Regional breakdown
   479    region_revenue = defaultdict(float)
   480    for row in rows:
   481        region_revenue[row['region']] += row['total_sales']
   482
   483    top_region = max(region_revenue.items(), key=lambda x: x[1])
   484    bottom_region = min(region_revenue.items(), key=lambda x: x[1])
   485
   486    # Salesperson breakdown
   487    person_revenue = defaultdict(float)
   488    for row in rows:
   489        person_revenue[row['salesperson']] += row['total_sales']
   490
   491    top_salesperson = max(person_revenue.items(), key=lambda x: x[1])
   492
   493    print("BUSINESS PERFORMANCE")
   494    print(f" Total revenue of ${total_revenue:,.2f} across {len(rows)} transactions")
   495    print(f" Average transaction value: ${total_revenue/len(rows):,.2f}")
   496    print(f" Total units sold: {total_units:,}")
   497
   498    print("\nCATEGORY PERFORMANCE")
   499    print(f" {top_category[0]} leads with ${top_category[1]:,.2f} ({top_category[1]/total_revenue*100:.1f}%)")
   500    for cat, rev in sorted(cat_revenue.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True):
   501        print(f"  - {cat}: ${rev:,.2f} ({rev/total_revenue*100:.1f}%)")
   502
   503    print("\nREGIONAL PERFORMANCE")
   504    print(f" Best performing: {top_region[0]} (${top_region[1]:,.2f})")
   505    print(f" Needs attention: {bottom_region[0]} (${bottom_region[1]:,.2f})")
   506    gap = top_region[1] - bottom_region[1]
   507    print(f" Performance gap: ${gap:,.2f} ({gap/top_region[1]*100:.1f}%)")
   508
   509    print("\nSALES TEAM PERFORMANCE")
   510    print(f" Top performer: {top_salesperson[0]} (${top_salesperson[1]:,.2f})")
   511    avg_sales_per_person = total_revenue / len(person_revenue)
   512    print(f" Average per salesperson: ${avg_sales_per_person:,.2f}")

   515def main():
   516    """Main execution function."""
   517    print_section("COMPREHENSIVE DESCRIPTIVE ANALYTICS REPORT", "=")
   518    print(f"Generated: {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}")
   519
   520    # Load data
   521    try:
   522        rows = load_data('sales_data.csv')
   523    except FileNotFoundError:

   527    # Run all analyses

   532    analyze_by_salesperson(rows)
   533    analyze_products(rows)
   534    analyze_time_trends(rows)
   535    analyze_cross_tabulations(rows)

def analyze_by_category(rows: List[Dict]):
    """Analyze sales data by product category."""
    print_section("3. CATEGORY ANALYSIS")

    category_data = defaultdict(lambda: {
        'sales': [],
        'quantity': [],
        'transactions': 0,
        'products': set()
    })

    for row in rows:
        cat = row['category']
        category_data[cat]['sales'].append(row['total_sales'])
        category_data[cat]['quantity'].append(row['quantity'])
        category_data[cat]['transactions'] += 1
        category_data[cat]['products'].add(row['product'])

    for category in sorted(category_data.keys()):
        data = category_data[category]
        stats = calculate_descriptive_stats(data['sales'])

        print_subsection(f"{category}")
        print(f"Total Revenue:       ${stats['sum']:,.2f} ({stats['sum']/sum(r['total_sales'] for r in rows)*100:.1f}%)")
        print(f"Transactions:        {data['transactions']} ({data['transactions']/len(rows)*100:.1f}%)")
        print(f"Unique Products:     {len(data['products'])}")
        print(f"Total Units:         {sum(data['quantity']):,}")
        print(f"Avg Transaction:     ${stats['mean']:,.2f}")
        print(f"Median Transaction:  ${stats['median']:,.2f}")
        print(f"Avg Units/Order:     {statistics.mean(data['quantity']):.1f}")

def plot_category_analysis(category_data: Dict, rows: List[Dict]):
    """Create visualizations for category analysis."""
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))
    fig.suptitle('Category Performance Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

    # Revenue by category (bar chart)
    categories = sorted(category_data.keys())
    revenues = [sum(category_data[cat]['sales']) for cat in categories]

    axes[0, 0].bar(categories, revenues, color=['#2E86AB', '#A23B72'])
    axes[0, 0].set_title('Total Revenue by Category')
    axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Revenue ($)')
    axes[0, 0].ticklabel_format(style='plain', axis='y')
    for i, v in enumerate(revenues):
        axes[0, 0].text(i, v, f'${v:,.0f}', ha='center', va='bottom')

    # Transaction count by category
    transactions = [category_data[cat]['transactions'] for cat in categories]
    axes[0, 1].bar(categories, transactions, color=['#2E86AB', '#A23B72'])
    axes[0, 1].set_title('Transaction Count by Category')
    axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Number of Transactions')
    for i, v in enumerate(transactions):
        axes[0, 1].text(i, v, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom')

    # Box plot of transaction values by category
    sales_by_cat = [category_data[cat]['sales'] for cat in categories]
    bp = axes[1, 0].boxplot(sales_by_cat, labels=categories, patch_artist=True)
    for patch, color in zip(bp['boxes'], ['#2E86AB', '#A23B72']):
        patch.set_facecolor(color)
    axes[1, 0].set_title('Distribution of Transaction Values')
    axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Transaction Value ($)')
    axes[1, 0].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)

    # Pie chart of revenue share
    axes[1, 1].pie(revenues, labels=categories, autopct='%1.1f%%',
                    colors=['#2E86AB', '#A23B72'], startangle=90)
    axes[1, 1].set_title('Revenue Share by Category')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


def plot_regional_analysis(region_data: Dict):
    """Create visualizations for regional analysis."""
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))
    fig.suptitle('Regional Performance Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

    regions = sorted(region_data.keys())
    revenues = [sum(region_data[r]['sales']) for r in regions]
    quantities = [sum(region_data[r]['quantity']) for r in regions]
    transactions = [region_data[r]['transactions'] for r in regions]

    colors = ['#F18F01', '#C73E1D', '#6A994E', '#2E86AB']

    # Revenue by region
    bars = axes[0, 0].bar(regions, revenues, color=colors)
    axes[0, 0].set_title('Total Revenue by Region')
    axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Revenue ($)')
    axes[0, 0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
    for bar in bars:
        height = bar.get_height()
        axes[0, 0].text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height,
                        f'${height:,.0f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=9)

    # Units sold by region
    axes[0, 1].bar(regions, quantities, color=colors)
    axes[0, 1].set_title('Total Units Sold by Region')
    axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Units Sold')
    axes[0, 1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

    # Average transaction value by region
    avg_trans = [sum(region_data[r]['sales'])/region_data[r]['transactions'] for r in regions]
    axes[1, 0].bar(regions, avg_trans, color=colors)
    axes[1, 0].set_title('Average Transaction Value by Region')
    axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Avg Transaction ($)')
    axes[1, 0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
    for i, v in enumerate(avg_trans):
        axes[1, 0].text(i, v, f'${v:,.0f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=9)

    # Transaction count by region
    axes[1, 1].bar(regions, transactions, color=colors)
    axes[1, 1].set_title('Transaction Count by Region')
    axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('Number of Transactions')
    axes[1, 1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


def plot_salesperson_performance(salesperson_data: Dict):
    """Create visualizations for salesperson performance."""
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))
    fig.suptitle('Salesperson Performance Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

    # Sort by revenue
    sorted_sales = sorted(salesperson_data.items(),
                         key=lambda x: sum(x[1]['sales']), reverse=True)
    salespeople = [s[0] for s in sorted_sales]
    revenues = [sum(s[1]['sales']) for s in sorted_sales]
    quantities = [sum(s[1]['quantity']) for s in sorted_sales]
    transactions = [s[1]['transactions'] for s in sorted_sales]

    colors = ['#2E86AB', '#A23B72', '#F18F01', '#6A994E']

    # Revenue by salesperson
    bars = axes[0, 0].barh(salespeople, revenues, color=colors)
    axes[0, 0].set_title('Total Revenue by Salesperson')
    axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Revenue ($)')
    for i, bar in enumerate(bars):
        width = bar.get_width()
        axes[0, 0].text(width, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2.,
                        f'${width:,.0f}', ha='left', va='center', fontsize=9)

    # Units sold by salesperson
    axes[0, 1].barh(salespeople, quantities, color=colors)
    axes[0, 1].set_title('Total Units Sold by Salesperson')
    axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Units Sold')

    # Average transaction value
    avg_trans = [revenues[i]/transactions[i] for i in range(len(salespeople))]
    axes[1, 0].barh(salespeople, avg_trans, color=colors)
    axes[1, 0].set_title('Average Transaction Value')
    axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Avg Transaction ($)')
    for i, v in enumerate(avg_trans):
        axes[1, 0].text(v, i, f'${v:,.0f}', ha='left', va='center', fontsize=9)

    # Revenue per unit
    rev_per_unit = [revenues[i]/quantities[i] for i in range(len(salespeople))]
    axes[1, 1].barh(salespeople, rev_per_unit, color=colors)
    axes[1, 1].set_title('Revenue per Unit Sold')
    axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Revenue per Unit ($)')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


def plot_product_analysis(rows: List[Dict]):
    """Create visualizations for product analysis."""
    # Aggregate product data
    product_data = defaultdict(lambda: {'sales': 0, 'quantity': 0})
    for row in rows:
        product_data[row['product']]['sales'] += row['total_sales']
        product_data[row['product']]['quantity'] += row['quantity']

    # Top 10 products by revenue
    top_products_rev = sorted(product_data.items(),
                              key=lambda x: x[1]['sales'], reverse=True)[:10]

    # Top 10 products by quantity
    top_products_qty = sorted(product_data.items(),
                              key=lambda x: x[1]['quantity'], reverse=True)[:10]

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 6))
    fig.suptitle('Product Performance Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

    # Top products by revenue
    products_rev = [p[0][:20] for p in top_products_rev]  # Truncate names
    revenues = [p[1]['sales'] for p in top_products_rev]

    axes[0].barh(products_rev, revenues, color='#2E86AB')
    axes[0].set_title('Top 10 Products by Revenue')
    axes[0].set_xlabel('Revenue ($)')
    axes[0].invert_yaxis()
    for i, v in enumerate(revenues):
        axes[0].text(v, i, f'${v:,.0f}', ha='left', va='center', fontsize=8)

    # Top products by quantity
    products_qty = [p[0][:20] for p in top_products_qty]
    quantities = [p[1]['quantity'] for p in top_products_qty]

    axes[1].barh(products_qty, quantities, color='#A23B72')
    axes[1].set_title('Top 10 Products by Quantity Sold')
    axes[1].set_xlabel('Units Sold')
    axes[1].invert_yaxis()
    for i, v in enumerate(quantities):
        axes[1].text(v, i, f'{v}', ha='left', va='center', fontsize=8)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


def plot_time_trends(rows: List[Dict]):
    """Create visualizations for time-based analysis."""
    # Aggregate daily data
    daily_data = defaultdict(lambda: {'sales': 0, 'quantity': 0, 'transactions': 0})
    for row in rows:
        daily_data[row['date']]['sales'] += row['total_sales']
        daily_data[row['date']]['quantity'] += row['quantity']
        daily_data[row['date']]['transactions'] += 1

    # Sort by date
    sorted_days = sorted(daily_data.items())
    dates = [d[0] for d in sorted_days]
    sales = [d[1]['sales'] for d in sorted_days]
    quantities = [d[1]['quantity'] for d in sorted_days]
    transactions = [d[1]['transactions'] for d in sorted_days]

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(14, 10))
    fig.suptitle('Daily Sales Trends', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

    # Daily revenue
    axes[0].plot(dates, sales, marker='o', linewidth=2, color='#2E86AB')
    axes[0].fill_between(range(len(dates)), sales, alpha=0.3, color='#2E86AB')
    axes[0].set_title('Daily Revenue')
    axes[0].set_ylabel('Revenue ($)')
    axes[0].grid(alpha=0.3)
    axes[0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

    # Daily units sold
    axes[1].bar(dates, quantities, color='#A23B72', alpha=0.7)
    axes[1].set_title('Daily Units Sold')
    axes[1].set_ylabel('Units Sold')
    axes[1].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
    axes[1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

    # Daily transaction count
    axes[2].bar(dates, transactions, color='#F18F01', alpha=0.7)
    axes[2].set_title('Daily Transaction Count')
    axes[2].set_ylabel('Number of Transactions')
    axes[2].set_xlabel('Date')
    axes[2].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
    axes[2].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


def plot_distributions(rows: List[Dict]):
    """Create distribution visualizations."""
    sales_values = [row['total_sales'] for row in rows]
    quantities = [row['quantity'] for row in rows]
    unit_prices = [row['unit_price'] for row in rows]

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))
    fig.suptitle('Distribution Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

    # Histogram of sales values
    axes[0, 0].hist(sales_values, bins=15, color='#2E86AB', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    axes[0, 0].axvline(np.mean(sales_values), color='red', linestyle='--',
                       linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: ${np.mean(sales_values):,.0f}')
    axes[0, 0].axvline(np.median(sales_values), color='green', linestyle='--',
                       linewidth=2, label=f'Median: ${np.median(sales_values):,.0f}')
    axes[0, 0].set_title('Distribution of Transaction Values')
    axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Transaction Value ($)')
    axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Frequency')
    axes[0, 0].legend()
    axes[0, 0].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)

    # Histogram of quantities
    axes[0, 1].hist(quantities, bins=15, color='#A23B72', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    axes[0, 1].axvline(np.mean(quantities), color='red', linestyle='--',
                       linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: {np.mean(quantities):.1f}')
    axes[0, 1].set_title('Distribution of Order Quantities')
    axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Quantity')
    axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Frequency')
    axes[0, 1].legend()
    axes[0, 1].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)

    # Histogram of unit prices
    axes[1, 0].hist(unit_prices, bins=15, color='#F18F01', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    axes[1, 0].axvline(np.mean(unit_prices), color='red', linestyle='--',
                       linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: ${np.mean(unit_prices):,.0f}')
    axes[1, 0].set_title('Distribution of Unit Prices')
    axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Unit Price ($)')
    axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Frequency')
    axes[1, 0].legend()
    axes[1, 0].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)

    # Scatter plot: Quantity vs Total Sales
    axes[1, 1].scatter(quantities, sales_values, alpha=0.6, s=100, c='#6A994E')
    axes[1, 1].set_title('Quantity vs. Total Sales')
    axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Quantity')
    axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('Total Sales ($)')
    axes[1, 1].grid(alpha=0.3)

    # Add correlation coefficient
    corr = np.corrcoef(quantities, sales_values)[0, 1]
    axes[1, 1].text(0.05, 0.95, f'Correlation: {corr:.3f}',
                    transform=axes[1, 1].transAxes, verticalalignment='top',
                    bbox=dict(boxstyle='round', facecolor='wheat', alpha=0.5))

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


def plot_cross_tabulation(rows: List[Dict]):
    """Create heatmap for category  region analysis."""
    # Build cross-tabulation matrix
    cross_tab = defaultdict(lambda: defaultdict(float))
    for row in rows:
        cross_tab[row['category']][row['region']] += row['total_sales']

    categories = sorted(cross_tab.keys())
    regions = sorted(set(row['region'] for row in rows))

    # Create matrix
    matrix = np.zeros((len(categories), len(regions)))
    for i, cat in enumerate(categories):
        for j, region in enumerate(regions):
            matrix[i, j] = cross_tab[cat][region]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    im = ax.imshow(matrix, cmap='YlOrRd', aspect='auto')

    # Set ticks and labels
    ax.set_xticks(np.arange(len(regions)))
    ax.set_yticks(np.arange(len(categories)))
    ax.set_xticklabels(regions)
    ax.set_yticklabels(categories)

    # Rotate the tick labels
    plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right", rotation_mode="anchor")

    # Add colorbar
    cbar = plt.colorbar(im, ax=ax)
    cbar.set_label('Revenue ($)', rotation=270, labelpad=20)

    # Add text annotations
    for i in range(len(categories)):
        for j in range(len(regions)):
            text = ax.text(j, i, f'${matrix[i, j]:,.0f}',
                          ha="center", va="center", color="black", fontsize=10)

    ax.set_title('Revenue Heatmap: Category  Region', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', pad=20)
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Category')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

   194def plot_regional_analysis(region_data: Dict):
   195    """Create visualizations for regional analysis."""
   196    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))
   197    fig.suptitle('Regional Performance Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
   198
   199    regions = sorted(region_data.keys())
   200    revenues = [sum(region_data[r]['sales']) for r in regions]
   201    quantities = [sum(region_data[r]['quantity']) for r in regions]
   202    transactions = [region_data[r]['transactions'] for r in regions]
   203
   204    colors = ['#F18F01', '#C73E1D', '#6A994E', '#2E86AB']
   205
   206    # Revenue by region
   207    bars = axes[0, 0].bar(regions, revenues, color=colors)
   208    axes[0, 0].set_title('Total Revenue by Region')
   209    axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Revenue ($)')
   210    axes[0, 0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   211    for bar in bars:
   212        height = bar.get_height()
   213        axes[0, 0].text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height,
   214                        f'${height:,.0f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=9)
   215
   216    # Units sold by region
   217    axes[0, 1].bar(regions, quantities, color=colors)
   218    axes[0, 1].set_title('Total Units Sold by Region')
   219    axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Units Sold')
   220    axes[0, 1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   221
   222    # Average transaction value by region
   223    avg_trans = [sum(region_data[r]['sales'])/region_data[r]['transactions'] for r in regions]
   224    axes[1, 0].bar(regions, avg_trans, color=colors)
   225    axes[1, 0].set_title('Average Transaction Value by Region')
   226    axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Avg Transaction ($)')
   227    axes[1, 0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   228    for i, v in enumerate(avg_trans):
   229        axes[1, 0].text(i, v, f'${v:,.0f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=9)
   230
   231    # Transaction count by region
   232    axes[1, 1].bar(regions, transactions, color=colors)
   233    axes[1, 1].set_title('Transaction Count by Region')
   234    axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('Number of Transactions')
   235    axes[1, 1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

   241def plot_salesperson_performance(salesperson_data: Dict):
   242    """Create visualizations for salesperson performance."""
   243    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))
   244    fig.suptitle('Salesperson Performance Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
   245
   246    # Sort by revenue
   247    sorted_sales = sorted(salesperson_data.items(),
   248                         key=lambda x: sum(x[1]['sales']), reverse=True)
   249    salespeople = [s[0] for s in sorted_sales]
   250    revenues = [sum(s[1]['sales']) for s in sorted_sales]
   251    quantities = [sum(s[1]['quantity']) for s in sorted_sales]
   252    transactions = [s[1]['transactions'] for s in sorted_sales]
   253
   254    colors = ['#2E86AB', '#A23B72', '#F18F01', '#6A994E']
   255
   256    # Revenue by salesperson
   257    bars = axes[0, 0].barh(salespeople, revenues, color=colors)
   258    axes[0, 0].set_title('Total Revenue by Salesperson')
   259    axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Revenue ($)')
   260    for i, bar in enumerate(bars):
   261        width = bar.get_width()
   262        axes[0, 0].text(width, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2.,
   263                        f'${width:,.0f}', ha='left', va='center', fontsize=9)
   264
   265    # Units sold by salesperson
   266    axes[0, 1].barh(salespeople, quantities, color=colors)
   267    axes[0, 1].set_title('Total Units Sold by Salesperson')
   268    axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Units Sold')
   269
   270    # Average transaction value
   271    avg_trans = [revenues[i]/transactions[i] for i in range(len(salespeople))]
   272    axes[1, 0].barh(salespeople, avg_trans, color=colors)
   273    axes[1, 0].set_title('Average Transaction Value')
   274    axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Avg Transaction ($)')
   275    for i, v in enumerate(avg_trans):
   276        axes[1, 0].text(v, i, f'${v:,.0f}', ha='left', va='center', fontsize=9)
   277
   278    # Revenue per unit
   279    rev_per_unit = [revenues[i]/quantities[i] for i in range(len(salespeople))]
   280    axes[1, 1].barh(salespeople, rev_per_unit, color=colors)
   281    axes[1, 1].set_title('Revenue per Unit Sold')
   282    axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Revenue per Unit ($)')
   283
   284    plt.tight_layout()
   285    plt.show()

   288def plot_product_analysis(rows: List[Dict]):
   289    """Create visualizations for product analysis."""
   290    # Aggregate product data
   291    product_data = defaultdict(lambda: {'sales': 0, 'quantity': 0})
   292    for row in rows:
   293        product_data[row['product']]['sales'] += row['total_sales']
   294        product_data[row['product']]['quantity'] += row['quantity']
   295
   296    # Top 10 products by revenue
   297    top_products_rev = sorted(product_data.items(),
   298                              key=lambda x: x[1]['sales'], reverse=True)[:10]
   299
   300    # Top 10 products by quantity
   301    top_products_qty = sorted(product_data.items(),
   302                              key=lambda x: x[1]['quantity'], reverse=True)[:10]
   303
   304    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 6))
   305    fig.suptitle('Product Performance Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
   306
   307    # Top products by revenue
   308    products_rev = [p[0][:20] for p in top_products_rev]  # Truncate names
   309    revenues = [p[1]['sales'] for p in top_products_rev]
   310
   311    axes[0].barh(products_rev, revenues, color='#2E86AB')
   312    axes[0].set_title('Top 10 Products by Revenue')
   313    axes[0].set_xlabel('Revenue ($)')
   314    axes[0].invert_yaxis()
   315    for i, v in enumerate(revenues):
   316        axes[0].text(v, i, f'${v:,.0f}', ha='left', va='center', fontsize=8)
   317
   318    # Top products by quantity
   319    products_qty = [p[0][:20] for p in top_products_qty]
   320    quantities = [p[1]['quantity'] for p in top_products_qty]
   321
   322    axes[1].barh(products_qty, quantities, color='#A23B72')
   323    axes[1].set_title('Top 10 Products by Quantity Sold')
   324    axes[1].set_xlabel('Units Sold')
   325    axes[1].invert_yaxis()
   326    for i, v in enumerate(quantities):
   327        axes[1].text(v, i, f'{v}', ha='left', va='center', fontsize=8)
   328
   329    plt.tight_layout()
   330    plt.show()

   333def plot_time_trends(rows: List[Dict]):
   334    """Create visualizations for time-based analysis."""
   335    # Aggregate daily data
   336    daily_data = defaultdict(lambda: {'sales': 0, 'quantity': 0, 'transactions': 0})
   337    for row in rows:
   338        daily_data[row['date']]['sales'] += row['total_sales']
   339        daily_data[row['date']]['quantity'] += row['quantity']
   340        daily_data[row['date']]['transactions'] += 1
   341
   342    # Sort by date
   343    sorted_days = sorted(daily_data.items())
   344    dates = [d[0] for d in sorted_days]
   345    sales = [d[1]['sales'] for d in sorted_days]
   346    quantities = [d[1]['quantity'] for d in sorted_days]
   347    transactions = [d[1]['transactions'] for d in sorted_days]
   348
   349    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(14, 10))
   350    fig.suptitle('Daily Sales Trends', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
   351
   352    # Daily revenue
   353    axes[0].plot(dates, sales, marker='o', linewidth=2, color='#2E86AB')
   354    axes[0].fill_between(range(len(dates)), sales, alpha=0.3, color='#2E86AB')
   355    axes[0].set_title('Daily Revenue')
   356    axes[0].set_ylabel('Revenue ($)')
   357    axes[0].grid(alpha=0.3)
   358    axes[0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   359
   360    # Daily units sold
   361    axes[1].bar(dates, quantities, color='#A23B72', alpha=0.7)
   362    axes[1].set_title('Daily Units Sold')
   363    axes[1].set_ylabel('Units Sold')
   364    axes[1].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
   365    axes[1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   366
   367    # Daily transaction count
   368    axes[2].bar(dates, transactions, color='#F18F01', alpha=0.7)
   369    axes[2].set_title('Daily Transaction Count')
   370    axes[2].set_ylabel('Number of Transactions')
   371    axes[2].set_xlabel('Date')
   372    axes[2].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
   373    axes[2].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   374
   375    plt.tight_layout()
   376    plt.show()

   379def plot_distributions(rows: List[Dict]):
   380    """Create distribution visualizations."""
   381    sales_values = [row['total_sales'] for row in rows]
   382    quantities = [row['quantity'] for row in rows]
   383    unit_prices = [row['unit_price'] for row in rows]
   384
   385    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))
   386    fig.suptitle('Distribution Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
   387
   388    # Histogram of sales values
   389    axes[0, 0].hist(sales_values, bins=15, color='#2E86AB', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
   390    axes[0, 0].axvline(np.mean(sales_values), color='red', linestyle='--',
   391                       linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: ${np.mean(sales_values):,.0f}')
   392    axes[0, 0].axvline(np.median(sales_values), color='green', linestyle='--',
   393                       linewidth=2, label=f'Median: ${np.median(sales_values):,.0f}')
   394    axes[0, 0].set_title('Distribution of Transaction Values')
   395    axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Transaction Value ($)')
   396    axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Frequency')
   397    axes[0, 0].legend()
   398    axes[0, 0].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
   399
   400    # Histogram of quantities
   401    axes[0, 1].hist(quantities, bins=15, color='#A23B72', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
   402    axes[0, 1].axvline(np.mean(quantities), color='red', linestyle='--',
   403                       linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: {np.mean(quantities):.1f}')
   404    axes[0, 1].set_title('Distribution of Order Quantities')
   405    axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Quantity')
   406    axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Frequency')
   407    axes[0, 1].legend()
   408    axes[0, 1].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
   409
   410    # Histogram of unit prices
   411    axes[1, 0].hist(unit_prices, bins=15, color='#F18F01', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
   412    axes[1, 0].axvline(np.mean(unit_prices), color='red', linestyle='--',
   413                       linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: ${np.mean(unit_prices):,.0f}')
   414    axes[1, 0].set_title('Distribution of Unit Prices')
   415    axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Unit Price ($)')
   416    axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Frequency')
   417    axes[1, 0].legend()
   418    axes[1, 0].grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
   419
   420    # Scatter plot: Quantity vs Total Sales
   421    axes[1, 1].scatter(quantities, sales_values, alpha=0.6, s=100, c='#6A994E')
   422    axes[1, 1].set_title('Quantity vs. Total Sales')
   423    axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Quantity')
   424    axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('Total Sales ($)')
   425    axes[1, 1].grid(alpha=0.3)
   426
   427    # Add correlation coefficient
   428    corr = np.corrcoef(quantities, sales_values)[0, 1]
   429    axes[1, 1].text(0.05, 0.95, f'Correlation: {corr:.3f}',
   430                    transform=axes[1, 1].transAxes, verticalalignment='top',
   431                    bbox=dict(boxstyle='round', facecolor='wheat', alpha=0.5))
   432
   433    plt.tight_layout()
   434    plt.show()

   437def plot_cross_tabulation(rows: List[Dict]):
   438    """Create heatmap for category  region analysis."""
   439    # Build cross-tabulation matrix
   440    cross_tab = defaultdict(lambda: defaultdict(float))
   441    for row in rows:
   442        cross_tab[row['category']][row['region']] += row['total_sales']
   443
   444    categories = sorted(cross_tab.keys())
   445    regions = sorted(set(row['region'] for row in rows))
   446
   447    # Create matrix
   448    matrix = np.zeros((len(categories), len(regions)))
   449    for i, cat in enumerate(categories):
   450        for j, region in enumerate(regions):
   451            matrix[i, j] = cross_tab[cat][region]
   452
   453    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
   454    im = ax.imshow(matrix, cmap='YlOrRd', aspect='auto')
   455
   456    # Set ticks and labels
   457    ax.set_xticks(np.arange(len(regions)))
   458    ax.set_yticks(np.arange(len(categories)))
   459    ax.set_xticklabels(regions)
   460    ax.set_yticklabels(categories)
   461
   462    # Rotate the tick labels
   463    plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right", rotation_mode="anchor")
   464
   465    # Add colorbar
   466    cbar = plt.colorbar(im, ax=ax)
   467    cbar.set_label('Revenue ($)', rotation=270, labelpad=20)
   468
   469    # Add text annotations
   470    for i in range(len(categories)):
   471        for j in range(len(regions)):
   472            text = ax.text(j, i, f'${matrix[i, j]:,.0f}',
   473                          ha="center", va="center", color="black", fontsize=10)
   474
   475    ax.set_title('Revenue Heatmap: Category  Region', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', pad=20)
   476    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
   477    ax.set_ylabel('Category')
   478
   479    plt.tight_layout()
   480    plt.show()

# ============================================================================
# Descriptive Analytics for Sales Data (R Version)
# ============================================================================
# Comprehensive statistical analysis including data quality checks,
# descriptive statistics, distribution analysis, and multi-dimensional breakdowns.
#
# Author: Generated Analysis Script
# Date: 2024
# ============================================================================

# Load required libraries
library(tidyverse)    # Data manipulation and visualization
library(scales)       # Formatting scales
library(gridExtra)    # Arranging multiple plots
library(viridis)      # Color palettes
library(ggthemes)     # Additional themes

# Set theme for all plots
theme_set(theme_minimal(base_size = 12))

# ============================================================================
# DATA LOADING AND PREPARATION
# ============================================================================

load_sales_data <- function(filename) {
  #' Load and parse sales data from CSV file
  #'
  #' @param filename Path to CSV file
  #' @return Data frame containing parsed sales records

  data <- read_csv(filename, show_col_types = FALSE) %>%
    mutate(
      date = as.Date(date),
      product = as.character(product),
      category = as.factor(category),
      quantity = as.integer(quantity),
      unit_price = as.numeric(unit_price),
      total_sales = as.numeric(total_sales),
      region = as.factor(region),
      salesperson = as.factor(salesperson)
    )

  return(data)
}


# ============================================================================
# UTILITY FUNCTIONS
# ============================================================================

print_section <- function(title, char = "=") {
  #' Print formatted section header
  width <- 80
  cat("\n", strrep(char, width), "\n", sep = "")
  cat(format(title, width = width, justify = "centre"), "\n")
  cat(strrep(char, width), "\n\n", sep = "")
}

print_subsection <- function(title) {
  #' Print formatted subsection header
  cat("\n", title, "\n", sep = "")
  cat(strrep("-", nchar(title)), "\n", sep = "")
}

calculate_descriptive_stats <- function(values) {
  #' Calculate comprehensive descriptive statistics
  #'
  #' @param values Numeric vector
  #' @return List containing statistical measures

  list(
    count = length(values),
    sum = sum(values, na.rm = TRUE),
    mean = mean(values, na.rm = TRUE),
    median = median(values, na.rm = TRUE),
    std_dev = sd(values, na.rm = TRUE),
    min = min(values, na.rm = TRUE),
    max = max(values, na.rm = TRUE),
    q1 = quantile(values, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),
    q3 = quantile(values, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
    range = max(values, na.rm = TRUE) - min(values, na.rm = TRUE)
  )
}


# ============================================================================
# DATA QUALITY CHECKS
# ============================================================================

data_quality_check <- function(data) {
  #' Perform comprehensive data quality checks
  #'
  #' @param data Sales data frame
  #' @return List containing quality check results

  issues <- c()
  warnings <- c()

  # Check for missing values
  missing_counts <- colSums(is.na(data))
  if (any(missing_counts > 0)) {
    for (col in names(missing_counts[missing_counts > 0])) {
      issues <- c(issues, sprintf("Column '%s': %d missing values", col, missing_counts[col]))
    }
  }

  # Validate calculations
  calculation_errors <- 0
  for (i in 1:nrow(data)) {
    expected <- round(data$quantity[i] * data$unit_price[i], 2)
    actual <- round(data$total_sales[i], 2)
    if (abs(expected - actual) > 0.02) {
      calculation_errors <- calculation_errors + 1
      warnings <- c(warnings, sprintf(
        "Row %d: Calculation mismatch - %d  $%.2f = $%.2f, but total_sales = $%.2f",
        i, data$quantity[i], data$unit_price[i], expected, actual
      ))
    }
  }

  # Check for negative values
  if (any(data$quantity < 0, na.rm = TRUE)) {
    issues <- c(issues, "Negative quantity values found")
  }
  if (any(data$unit_price < 0, na.rm = TRUE)) {
    issues <- c(issues, "Negative unit price values found")
  }
  if (any(data$total_sales < 0, na.rm = TRUE)) {
    issues <- c(issues, "Negative total sales values found")
  }

  # Check for outliers
  mean_sales <- mean(data$total_sales, na.rm = TRUE)
  std_sales <- sd(data$total_sales, na.rm = TRUE)
  threshold <- 3 * std_sales

  outliers <- sum(abs(data$total_sales - mean_sales) > threshold, na.rm = TRUE)
  if (outliers > 0) {
    warnings <- c(warnings, sprintf("Found %d statistical outliers (>3 std dev)", outliers))
  }

  list(
    total_rows = nrow(data),
    issues = issues,
    warnings = warnings,
    calculation_errors = calculation_errors,
    is_clean = length(issues) == 0
  )
}


# ============================================================================
# ANALYSIS FUNCTIONS
# ============================================================================

analyze_overall_metrics <- function(data) {
  #' Analyze and display overall dataset metrics

  print_section("1. DATA OVERVIEW & QUALITY")

  # Basic info
  print_subsection("Dataset Information")
  cat(sprintf("Total Records: %d\n", nrow(data)))
  cat(sprintf("Date Range: %s to %s\n", min(data$date), max(data$date)))
  cat(sprintf("Unique Products: %d\n", n_distinct(data$product)))
  cat(sprintf("Categories: %s\n", paste(levels(data$category), collapse = ", ")))
  cat(sprintf("Regions: %s\n", paste(sort(levels(data$region)), collapse = ", ")))
  cat(sprintf("Salespeople: %s\n", paste(sort(levels(data$salesperson)), collapse = ", ")))

  # Data quality
  print_subsection("Data Quality Check")
  quality <- data_quality_check(data)

  if (quality$is_clean) {
    cat(" Data validation PASSED - No issues found\n")
  } else {
    cat(sprintf(" Data validation FAILED - %d issues found\n", length(quality$issues)))
    for (issue in head(quality$issues, 5)) {
      cat(sprintf("  - %s\n", issue))
    }
  }

  if (length(quality$warnings) > 0) {
    cat(sprintf("\n %d warnings:\n", length(quality$warnings)))
    for (warning in head(quality$warnings, 5)) {
      cat(sprintf("  - %s\n", warning))
    }
  }
}


analyze_descriptive_statistics <- function(data) {
  #' Calculate and display descriptive statistics

  print_section("2. DESCRIPTIVE STATISTICS")

  # Sales statistics
  print_subsection("Total Sales Statistics")
  sales_stats <- calculate_descriptive_stats(data$total_sales)
  cat(sprintf("Count:                %d\n", sales_stats$count))
  cat(sprintf("Sum:                  $%s\n", format(sales_stats$sum, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Mean:                 $%s\n", format(sales_stats$mean, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Median:               $%s\n", format(sales_stats$median, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Std Deviation:        $%s\n", format(sales_stats$std_dev, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Min:                  $%s\n", format(sales_stats$min, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Q1 (25th percentile): $%s\n", format(sales_stats$q1, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Q3 (75th percentile): $%s\n", format(sales_stats$q3, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Max:                  $%s\n", format(sales_stats$max, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Range:                $%s\n", format(sales_stats$range, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))

  # Quantity statistics
  print_subsection("Quantity Statistics")
  qty_stats <- calculate_descriptive_stats(data$quantity)
  cat(sprintf("Total Units Sold:   %s\n", format(qty_stats$sum, big.mark = ",")))
  cat(sprintf("Mean per Order:     %.1f\n", qty_stats$mean))
  cat(sprintf("Median per Order:   %.0f\n", qty_stats$median))
  cat(sprintf("Std Deviation:      %.2f\n", qty_stats$std_dev))
  cat(sprintf("Min Order:          %d\n", qty_stats$min))
  cat(sprintf("Max Order:          %d\n", qty_stats$max))

  # Unit price statistics
  print_subsection("Unit Price Statistics")
  price_stats <- calculate_descriptive_stats(data$unit_price)
  cat(sprintf("Mean Price:         $%s\n", format(price_stats$mean, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Median Price:       $%s\n", format(price_stats$median, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Std Deviation:      $%s\n", format(price_stats$std_dev, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Lowest Price:       $%s\n", format(price_stats$min, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Highest Price:      $%s\n", format(price_stats$max, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))

  # Average order value
  print_subsection("Order Metrics")
  cat(sprintf("Average Order Value: $%s\n", format(sales_stats$mean, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Median Order Value:  $%s\n", format(sales_stats$median, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
}


analyze_by_category <- function(data) {
  #' Analyze sales data by product category

  print_section("3. CATEGORY ANALYSIS")

  category_summary <- data %>%
    group_by(category) %>%
    summarise(
      total_revenue = sum(total_sales),
      transactions = n(),
      unique_products = n_distinct(product),
      total_units = sum(quantity),
      avg_transaction = mean(total_sales),
      median_transaction = median(total_sales),
      avg_units_per_order = mean(quantity),
      .groups = "drop"
    )

  total_revenue <- sum(data$total_sales)
  total_transactions <- nrow(data)

  for (i in 1:nrow(category_summary)) {
    cat <- category_summary$category[i]
    print_subsection(as.character(cat))
    cat(sprintf("Total Revenue:       $%s (%.1f%%)\n",
                format(category_summary$total_revenue[i], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2),
                category_summary$total_revenue[i] / total_revenue * 100))
    cat(sprintf("Transactions:        %d (%.1f%%)\n",
                category_summary$transactions[i],
                category_summary$transactions[i] / total_transactions * 100))
    cat(sprintf("Unique Products:     %d\n", category_summary$unique_products[i]))
    cat(sprintf("Total Units:         %s\n", format(category_summary$total_units[i], big.mark = ",")))
    cat(sprintf("Avg Transaction:     $%s\n", format(category_summary$avg_transaction[i], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
    cat(sprintf("Median Transaction:  $%s\n", format(category_summary$median_transaction[i], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
    cat(sprintf("Avg Units/Order:     %.1f\n", category_summary$avg_units_per_order[i]))
  }
}


analyze_by_region <- function(data) {
  #' Analyze sales performance by region

  print_section("4. REGIONAL ANALYSIS")

  region_summary <- data %>%
    group_by(region) %>%
    summarise(
      total_revenue = sum(total_sales),
      transactions = n(),
      total_units = sum(quantity),
      avg_transaction = mean(total_sales),
      median_transaction = median(total_sales),
      .groups = "drop"
    ) %>%
    arrange(desc(total_revenue))

  total_revenue <- sum(data$total_sales)

  for (i in 1:nrow(region_summary)) {
    reg <- region_summary$region[i]
    print_subsection(sprintf("%s Region", as.character(reg)))
    cat(sprintf("Total Revenue:       $%s (%.1f%%)\n",
                format(region_summary$total_revenue[i], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2),
                region_summary$total_revenue[i] / total_revenue * 100))
    cat(sprintf("Transactions:        %d\n", region_summary$transactions[i]))
    cat(sprintf("Total Units:         %s\n", format(region_summary$total_units[i], big.mark = ",")))
    cat(sprintf("Avg Transaction:     $%s\n", format(region_summary$avg_transaction[i], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
    cat(sprintf("Median Transaction:  $%s\n", format(region_summary$median_transaction[i], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))

    # Category mix for this region
    cat_mix <- data %>%
      filter(region == reg) %>%
      count(category, name = "count")
    cat("Category Mix:        ")
    cat(paste(sprintf("%s (%d)", cat_mix$category, cat_mix$count), collapse = " "))
    cat("\n")
  }
}

analyze_time_trends <- function(data) {

    ) %>%

  print_subsection("Daily Sales Summary")
  daily_stats <- calculate_descriptive_stats(daily_summary$total_sales)
  cat(sprintf("Number of Days:      %d\n", nrow(daily_summary)))

  cat(sprintf("Median Daily Sales:  $%s\n", format(daily_stats$median, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Std Deviation:       $%s\n", format(daily_stats$std_dev, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Best Day Sales:      $%s\n", format(daily_stats$max, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf("Worst Day Sales:     $%s\n", format(daily_stats$min, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))

  print_subsection("Top 5 Days by Revenue")
  top_days <- daily_summary %>%
    arrange(desc(total_sales)) %>%

  for (i in 1:nrow(top_days)) {
    cat(sprintf("%d. %s: $%10s (%d transactions)\n",
                i,
                top_days$date[i],
                format(top_days$total_sales[i], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2),
                top_days$transactions[i]))
  }
}


analyze_cross_tabulations <- function(data) {
  #' Perform cross-tabulation analysis

  print_section("8. CROSS-TABULATION ANALYSIS")

  print_subsection("Revenue by Category  Region")

  cross_tab <- data %>%
    group_by(category, region) %>%
    summarise(revenue = sum(total_sales), .groups = "drop") %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = region, values_from = revenue, values_fill = 0)

  # Calculate totals
  cross_tab <- cross_tab %>%
    mutate(Total = rowSums(select(., -category)))

  # Print header
  cat(sprintf("%-15s", "Category"))
  for (col in names(cross_tab)[-1]) {
    cat(sprintf("%12s", col))
  }
  cat("\n")
  cat(strrep("-", 15 + 12 * (ncol(cross_tab) - 1)), "\n")

  # Print data
  for (i in 1:nrow(cross_tab)) {
    cat(sprintf("%-15s", cross_tab$category[i]))
    for (col in names(cross_tab)[-1]) {
      cat(sprintf("$%10.0f ", cross_tab[[col]][i]))
    }
    cat("\n")
  }
}


generate_summary_insights <- function(data) {
  #' Generate key insights and summary statistics

  print_section("9. KEY INSIGHTS & SUMMARY")

  total_revenue <- sum(data$total_sales)
  total_units <- sum(data$quantity)
  total_transactions <- nrow(data)

  # Category breakdown
  cat_revenue <- data %>%
    group_by(category) %>%
    summarise(revenue = sum(total_sales), .groups = "drop") %>%
    arrange(desc(revenue))

  # Regional breakdown
  region_revenue <- data %>%
    group_by(region) %>%
    summarise(revenue = sum(total_sales), .groups = "drop") %>%
    arrange(desc(revenue))

  # Salesperson breakdown
  person_revenue <- data %>%
    group_by(salesperson) %>%
    summarise(revenue = sum(total_sales), .groups = "drop") %>%
    arrange(desc(revenue))

  cat("BUSINESS PERFORMANCE\n")
  cat(sprintf(" Total revenue of $%s across %d transactions\n",
              format(total_revenue, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2), total_transactions))
  cat(sprintf(" Average transaction value: $%s\n",
              format(total_revenue / total_transactions, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf(" Total units sold: %s\n", format(total_units, big.mark = ",")))

  cat("\nCATEGORY PERFORMANCE\n")
  cat(sprintf(" %s leads with $%s (%.1f%%)\n",
              cat_revenue$category[1],
              format(cat_revenue$revenue[1], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2),
              cat_revenue$revenue[1] / total_revenue * 100))
  for (i in 1:nrow(cat_revenue)) {
    cat(sprintf("  - %s: $%s (%.1f%%)\n",
                cat_revenue$category[i],
                format(cat_revenue$revenue[i], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2),
                cat_revenue$revenue[i] / total_revenue * 100))
  }

  cat("\nREGIONAL PERFORMANCE\n")
  cat(sprintf(" Best performing: %s ($%s)\n",
              region_revenue$region[1],
              format(region_revenue$revenue[1], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf(" Needs attention: %s ($%s)\n",
              region_revenue$region[nrow(region_revenue)],
              format(region_revenue$revenue[nrow(region_revenue)], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  gap <- region_revenue$revenue[1] - region_revenue$revenue[nrow(region_revenue)]
  cat(sprintf(" Performance gap: $%s (%.1f%%)\n",
              format(gap, big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2),
              gap / region_revenue$revenue[1] * 100))

  cat("\nSALES TEAM PERFORMANCE\n")
  cat(sprintf(" Top performer: %s ($%s)\n",
              person_revenue$salesperson[1],
              format(person_revenue$revenue[1], big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
  cat(sprintf(" Average per salesperson: $%s\n",
              format(mean(person_revenue$revenue), big.mark = ",", nsmall = 2)))
}


# ============================================================================

plot_distributions <- function(data) {
  #' Create distribution visualizations

  p1 <- ggplot(data, aes(x = total_sales)) +
    geom_histogram(bins = 15, fill = "#2E86AB", alpha = 0.7, color = "black") +
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(total_sales)), color = "red",
               linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept = median(total_sales)), color = "green",
               linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
    labs(title = "Distribution of Transaction Values",
         x = "Transaction Value ($)", y = "Frequency") +
    scale_x_continuous(labels = dollar_format()) +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p2 <- ggplot(data, aes(x = quantity)) +
    geom_histogram(bins = 15, fill = "#A23B72", alpha = 0.7, color = "black") +
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(quantity)), color = "red",
               linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
    labs(title = "Distribution of Order Quantities",
         x = "Quantity", y = "Frequency") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p3 <- ggplot(data, aes(x = unit_price)) +
    geom_histogram(bins = 15, fill = "#F18F01", alpha = 0.7, color = "black") +
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(unit_price)), color = "red",
               linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
    labs(title = "Distribution of Unit Prices",
         x = "Unit Price ($)", y = "Frequency") +
    scale_x_continuous(labels = dollar_format()) +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p4 <- ggplot(data, aes(x = quantity, y = total_sales)) +
    geom_point(alpha = 0.6, size = 3, color = "#6A994E") +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "red", linetype = "dashed") +
    labs(title = sprintf("Quantity vs. Total Sales (r = %.3f)",
                         cor(data$quantity, data$total_sales)),
         x = "Quantity", y = "Total Sales ($)") +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format()) +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, p4, ncol = 2,
               top = textGrob("Distribution Analysis",
                             gp = gpar(fontsize = 16, fontface = "bold")))
}


plot_category_analysis <- function(data) {
  #' Create visualizations for category analysis

  category_summary <- data %>%
    group_by(category) %>%
    summarise(
      revenue = sum(total_sales),
      transactions = n(),
      .groups = "drop"
    )

  p1 <- ggplot(category_summary, aes(x = category, y = revenue, fill = category)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    geom_text(aes(label = dollar(revenue, accuracy = 1)), vjust = -0.5) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("#2E86AB", "#A23B72")) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format(), expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1))) +
    labs(title = "Total Revenue by Category", x = "Category", y = "Revenue ($)") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p2 <- ggplot(category_summary, aes(x = category, y = transactions, fill = category)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    geom_text(aes(label = transactions), vjust = -0.5) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("#2E86AB", "#A23B72")) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1))) +
    labs(title = "Transaction Count by Category", x = "Category", y = "Transactions") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p3 <- ggplot(data, aes(x = category, y = total_sales, fill = category)) +
    geom_boxplot(show.legend = FALSE) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("#2E86AB", "#A23B72")) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format()) +
    labs(title = "Distribution of Transaction Values", x = "Category", y = "Transaction Value ($)") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p4 <- ggplot(category_summary, aes(x = "", y = revenue, fill = category)) +
    geom_col(width = 1) +
    coord_polar(theta = "y") +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("#2E86AB", "#A23B72")) +
    geom_text(aes(label = percent(revenue/sum(revenue), accuracy = 0.1)),
              position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5)) +
    labs(title = "Revenue Share by Category", fill = "Category") +
    theme_void() +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", hjust = 0.5))

  grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, p4, ncol = 2,
               top = textGrob("Category Performance Analysis",
                             gp = gpar(fontsize = 16, fontface = "bold")))
}


plot_regional_analysis <- function(data) {
  #' Create visualizations for regional analysis

  region_summary <- data %>%
    group_by(region) %>%
    summarise(
      revenue = sum(total_sales),
      units = sum(quantity),
      transactions = n(),
      avg_transaction = mean(total_sales),
      .groups = "drop"
    )

  colors <- c("#F18F01", "#C73E1D", "#6A994E", "#2E86AB")

  p1 <- ggplot(region_summary, aes(x = reorder(region, revenue), y = revenue, fill = region)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    geom_text(aes(label = dollar(revenue, accuracy = 1)), hjust = -0.1, size = 3) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format(), expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.15))) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Total Revenue by Region", x = "Region", y = "Revenue ($)") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p2 <- ggplot(region_summary, aes(x = reorder(region, units), y = units, fill = region)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Total Units Sold by Region", x = "Region", y = "Units Sold") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p3 <- ggplot(region_summary, aes(x = reorder(region, avg_transaction), y = avg_transaction, fill = region)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    geom_text(aes(label = dollar(avg_transaction, accuracy = 1)), hjust = -0.1, size = 3) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format(), expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.15))) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Average Transaction Value by Region", x = "Region", y = "Avg Transaction ($)") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p4 <- ggplot(region_summary, aes(x = reorder(region, transactions), y = transactions, fill = region)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Transaction Count by Region", x = "Region", y = "Transactions") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, p4, ncol = 2,
               top = textGrob("Regional Performance Analysis",
                             gp = gpar(fontsize = 16, fontface = "bold")))
}


plot_salesperson_performance <- function(data) {
  #' Create visualizations for salesperson performance

  salesperson_summary <- data %>%
    group_by(salesperson) %>%
    summarise(
      revenue = sum(total_sales),
      units = sum(quantity),
      transactions = n(),
      avg_transaction = mean(total_sales),
      revenue_per_unit = sum(total_sales) / sum(quantity),
      .groups = "drop"
    ) %>%
    arrange(desc(revenue))

  colors <- c("#2E86AB", "#A23B72", "#F18F01", "#6A994E")

  p1 <- ggplot(salesperson_summary, aes(x = reorder(salesperson, revenue), y = revenue, fill = salesperson)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    geom_text(aes(label = dollar(revenue, accuracy = 1)), hjust = -0.1, size = 3) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format(), expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.15))) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Total Revenue by Salesperson", x = "Salesperson", y = "Revenue ($)") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p2 <- ggplot(salesperson_summary, aes(x = reorder(salesperson, units), y = units, fill = salesperson)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Total Units Sold by Salesperson", x = "Salesperson", y = "Units Sold") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p3 <- ggplot(salesperson_summary, aes(x = reorder(salesperson, avg_transaction),
                                        y = avg_transaction, fill = salesperson)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    geom_text(aes(label = dollar(avg_transaction, accuracy = 1)), hjust = -0.1, size = 3) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format(), expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.15))) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Average Transaction Value", x = "Salesperson", y = "Avg Transaction ($)") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p4 <- ggplot(salesperson_summary, aes(x = reorder(salesperson, revenue_per_unit),
                                        y = revenue_per_unit, fill = salesperson)) +
    geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format()) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Revenue per Unit Sold", x = "Salesperson", y = "Revenue per Unit ($)") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, p4, ncol = 2,
               top = textGrob("Salesperson Performance Analysis",
                             gp = gpar(fontsize = 16, fontface = "bold")))
}


plot_product_analysis <- function(data) {
  #' Create visualizations for product analysis

  product_summary <- data %>%
    group_by(product) %>%
    summarise(
      revenue = sum(total_sales),
      quantity = sum(quantity),
      .groups = "drop"
    )

  top_revenue <- product_summary %>%
    arrange(desc(revenue)) %>%
    head(10) %>%
    mutate(product = str_trunc(product, 20))

  top_quantity <- product_summary %>%
    arrange(desc(quantity)) %>%
    head(10) %>%
    mutate(product = str_trunc(product, 20))

  p1 <- ggplot(top_revenue, aes(x = reorder(product, revenue), y = revenue)) +
    geom_col(fill = "#2E86AB") +
    geom_text(aes(label = dollar(revenue, accuracy = 1)), hjust = -0.1, size = 3) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format(), expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.15))) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Top 10 Products by Revenue", x = "Product", y = "Revenue ($)") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  p2 <- ggplot(top_quantity, aes(x = reorder(product, quantity), y = quantity)) +
    geom_col(fill = "#A23B72") +
    geom_text(aes(label = quantity), hjust = -0.1, size = 3) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.15))) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(title = "Top 10 Products by Quantity Sold", x = "Product", y = "Units Sold") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

  grid.arrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2,
               top = textGrob("Product Performance Analysis",
                             gp = gpar(fontsize = 16, fontface = "bold")))
}


plot_time_trends <- function(data) {
  #' Create visualizations for time-based analysis

  daily_summary <- data %>%
    group_by(date) %>%
    summarise(
      sales = sum(total_sales),
      quantity = sum(quantity),
      transactions = n(),
      .groups = "drop"
    ) %>%
    arrange(date)

  p1 <- ggplot(daily_summary, aes(x = date, y = sales)) +
    geom_line(color = "#2E86AB", size = 1.2) +
    geom_point(color = "#2E86AB", size = 2) +
    geom_area(alpha = 0.3, fill = "#2E86AB") +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = dollar_format()) +
    labs(title = "Daily Revenue", x = "Date", y = "Revenue ($)") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
          axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

  p2 <- ggplot(daily_summary, aes(x = date, y = quantity)) +
    geom_col(fill = "#A23B72", alpha = 0.7) +
    labs(title = "Daily Units Sold", x = "Date", y = "Units Sold") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
          axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

  p3 <- ggplot(daily_summary, aes(x = date, y = transactions)) +
    geom_col(fill = "#F18F01", alpha = 0.7) +
    labs(title = "Daily Transaction Count", x = "Date", y = "Transactions") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
          axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

  grid.arrange(p1, p2, p3, ncol = 1,
               top = textGrob("Daily Sales Trends",
                             gp = gpar(fontsize = 16, fontface = "bold")))
}


plot_cross_tabulation <- function(data) {
  #' Create heatmap for category  region analysis

  cross_tab <- data %>%
    group_by(category, region) %>%
    summarise(revenue = sum(total_sales), .groups = "drop")

  ggplot(cross_tab, aes(x = region, y = category, fill = revenue)) +
    geom_tile(color = "white") +
    geom_text(aes(label = dollar(revenue, accuracy = 1)), color = "black", size = 4) +
    scale_fill_gradient(low = "#FFF5EB", high = "#C73E1D", labels = dollar_format()) +
    labs(title = "Revenue Heatmap: Category  Region",
         x = "Region", y = "Category", fill = "Revenue ($)") +
    theme_minimal() +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", hjust = 0.5, size = 14),
          axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))
}


# ============================================================================
# MAIN EXECUTION
# ============================================================================

main <- function() {
  #' Main execution function

  print_section("COMPREHENSIVE DESCRIPTIVE ANALYTICS REPORT (R VERSION)", "=")
  cat(sprintf("Generated: %s\n", format(Sys.time(), "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")))

  # Load data
  tryCatch({
    data <- load_sales_data("sales_data.csv")
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Error: sales_data.csv not found!\n")
    return(NULL)
  })

  # Run all analyses
  analyze_overall_metrics(data)
  analyze_descriptive_statistics(data)

  # Create visualizations
  plot_distributions(data)

  analyze_by_category(data)
  plot_category_analysis(data)

  analyze_by_region(data)
  plot_regional_analysis(data)

  analyze_by_salesperson(data)
  plot_salesperson_performance(data)

  analyze_products(data)
  plot_product_analysis(data)

  analyze_time_trends(data)
  plot_time_trends(data)

  analyze_cross_tabulations(data)
  plot_cross_tabulation(data)

  generate_summary_insights(data)

  print_section("END OF REPORT", "=")
}


# Run the analysis
main()
